A: You are returning only the first image from the list. You need to iterate through the list and display each image.
Here is an example of how you can do this:
public void displayAllImages(ArrayList<Bitmap> bitmaps, ImageView imageView) {
    for (Bitmap bitmap : bitmaps) {
        imageView.setImageBitmap(bitmap);
        // Do something with the imageView, like add it to a layout or display it in a new activity
    }
}

In your activity, you can call this method:
ArrayList<Bitmap> bitmaps = db.getChamp_splash();
displayAllImages(bitmaps, imageView);

This will set the imageView to each bitmap in the list, one at a time.

A: You are returning only the last bitmap because you are not storing all the bitmaps in a list or array. You are just replacing the value of bitmap in each iteration of while loop.
You need to store all the bitmaps in a list or array and then return that list.
Here is the modified code:
public ArrayList<Bitmap> getChamp_splash() {
    ArrayList<Bitmap> bitmaps = new ArrayList<Bitmap>();
    SQLiteDatabase db = getReadableDatabase();
    db.beginTransaction();
    String sqlTables = "Champions";
    String selectQuery = "SELECT * FROM "+ sqlTables;
    Cursor c = db.rawQuery(selectQuery, null);
    if (c != null) {
        while (c.moveToNext()) {
            byte[] blob = c.getBlob(c.getColumnIndex("champ_splash"));
            Bitmap bitmap = BitmapFactory.decodeByteArray(blob, 0, blob.length);
            bitmaps.add(bitmap);
        }
    }
    db.setTransactionSuccessful();
    db.endTransaction();
    return bitmaps;
}

Then in your activity, you can get all the bitmaps and display them:
ArrayList<Bitmap> bitmaps = db.getChamp_splash();
for(Bitmap bitmap : bitmaps) {
    ImageView imageView = new ImageView(this);
    imageView.setImageBitmap(bitmap);
    // Add imageView to your layout
}

This will create a new ImageView for each bitmap and add it to your layout.

A: You are only storing the last bitmap in your list because you are replacing the bitmap in each iteration of your while loop. You need to store all the bitmaps in a list and then return that list.
Here is the modified code:
public ArrayList<Bitmap> getChamp_splash() {
    ArrayList<Bitmap> bitmaps = new ArrayList<Bitmap>();
    SQLiteDatabase db = getReadableDatabase();
    db.beginTransaction();
    String sqlTables = "Champions";
    String selectQuery = "SELECT * FROM "+ sqlTables;
    Cursor c = db.rawQuery(selectQuery, null);
    if (c != null) {
        while (c.moveToNext()) {
            byte[] blob = c.getBlob(c.getColumnIndex("champ_splash"));
            Bitmap bitmap = BitmapFactory.decodeByteArray(blob, 0, blob.length);
            bitmaps.add(bitmap);
        }
    }
    db.setTransactionSuccessful();
    db.endTransaction();
    return bitmaps;
}

Then in your activity, you can get all the bitmaps and display them:
